BTW, the links at the top of this form don&#x27;t lead to anywhere that seem to be able to help.

When I insert an image inline in an issue description or comment (ie by drag and drop into the image insert popup), the image displays in the field just fine. However, when I export the issues, those image files aren&#x27;t included in the export ZIP file.

The exported JSON for the description/comment containing the image includes the markdown that includes the image, like

{code}
![1523 test_noedit0.png](https://bitbucket.org/repo/pn5XgL/images/2038502625-1523%20test_noedit0.png)
{code}

but the actual image file is not in the ZIP file.

In Objective-C its a common convention to create extension files for a class, that contain a  &#x27;+&#x27; character in the middle of the filename, for example:\\
"NSError+MyProjectName.m"

When submitting a pull request with these files included, and browsing through the resulting diffs, I always get a message that the diff cannot be displayed:

{code}
#!obj-c

ProjectName/NSError+ProjectName.m
(i) While impressive, your diff is just too big!
{code}

"While impressive, your diff is just too big!"

These files are often very short, about 1-2k in size.
